1
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:58,100
Here are the steamed buns.

2
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:01,460
Here you go.

3
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:05,200
Eat slowly. They're fresh out of the pot.

4
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:06,400
Don't burn yourself.

5
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:10,060
You just ran out like that?

6
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,039
What else?

7
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:12,970
I couldn't help anyway.

8
00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:15,520
Staying there and arguing would just make me a nuisance.

9
00:01:15,520 --> 00:01:18,080
Forget it. It's not easy for anyone.

10
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:20,220
When I first came to Xinjiang,

11
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,000
the locals told me...

12
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:24,060
It has to go through three stages.

13
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,240
Want to know?

14
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:29,200
Ku, ku, and ku.

15
00:01:30,039 --> 00:01:31,640
What are you talking about?

16
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:33,360
It means

17
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,840
the local air is dry

18
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:37,840
and it's windy all year round.

19
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:39,360
People's skin

20
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:41,970
will definitely become dry and withered.

21
00:01:42,479 --> 00:01:44,280
That's the first 'ku'.

22
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:47,280
When outsiders start working here,

23
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:50,330
it's inevitable to encounter bumps and bruises.

24
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:52,000
Besides,

25
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,880
being thousands of miles away from home,

26
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:56,120
they must be psychologically fragile.

27
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,400
This is hardship.

28
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:05,960
Then there is also the cool part.

29
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,250
Since they are here,

30
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:09,039
and they have persisted.

31
00:02:09,440 --> 00:02:11,039
Don't you think that's cool?

32
00:02:14,080 --> 00:02:16,079
I just want to salvage the situation

33
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:18,500
and get things back on track quickly.

34
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,840
But he doesn't agree with me.

35
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:20,640
I understand.

36
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:22,160
Back then,

37
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:24,370
he didn't agree with me either.

38
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,220
When I first came to Xinjiang,

39
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,130
Teaching time is tight,

40
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,640
and the workload is heavy.

41
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:31,240
As for the kids in this class,

42
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:34,360
most only attended primary schools in pastoral areas.

43
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:36,420
Their foundation in Chinese is poor,

44
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:39,500
and their understanding of ancient poetry is average.

45
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,120
This Jiao Li

46
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,400
is the kid in class

47
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:44,800
who defies me the most.

48
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,400
Jiao Li,

49
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:04,400
can you write a few more words on the test paper?

50
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:07,120
This statue of yours,

51
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:09,200
I have seen it many times.

52
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:12,280
Don't laugh.

53
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,920
Nazahai is my good friend.

54
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:15,880
I miss it.

55
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,260
Jiao Li used to be so arrogant.

56
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:24,120
Mr. Yin, you aren't even mad about this?

57
00:03:24,480 --> 00:03:26,079
There are only bad teachers,

58
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:28,000
no bad students.

59
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:32,920
He was just a child in a new environment,

60
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,600
feeling overwhelmed

61
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,520
and insecure.

62
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:39,650
If I couldn't make him feel at ease,

63
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,120
how could he

64
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,930
enter the world of literature?

65
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:45,440
But it was exactly because of him

66
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:46,560
that I

67
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:48,980
wanted to change my teaching method.

68
00:03:50,079 --> 00:03:50,920
Secretary,

69
00:03:51,320 --> 00:03:53,640
you should go find Renzhen quickly.

70
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:57,880
Renzhen wasn't wrong about what happened yesterday either.

71
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,120
Renzhen?

72
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,160
What is this?

73
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,440
This was taken when I was in middle school

74
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:14,520
by Mr. Yin.

75
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:23,440
Mr. Yin, this is...

76
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:27,920
That is

77
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:30,440
a line I gave to Nazahai

78
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,580
from Su Shi's poem.

79
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,680
It's very fitting.

80
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,200
(2) The author saw a large lotus leaf next to the red lotus, slowly...

81
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,440
I hope you

82
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,930
and your good friend...

83
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:41,000
Everyone can experience the joy

84
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:42,840
of literature in your class.

85
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:58,240
The old man acting like a wild youth,

86
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:00,370
hound on the left, falcon on the right.

87
00:05:01,080 --> 00:05:02,080
You can recite it.

88
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:03,400
Teacher,

89
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:04,810
I really like this line.

90
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:06,570
Su Shi never visited Xinjiang,

91
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,360
but this line

92
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:09,600
seems to describe life on the grassland.

93
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,930
I understand this line,

94
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,080
but

95
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:14,640
there are many others I don't quite get.

96
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,160
Chinese,

97
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,200
is actually not that difficult.

98
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:21,440
As long as you bring it into your life

99
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:23,240
to identify with and embrace it,

100
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:25,720
you will resonate with

101
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,040
more ancient poetry.

102
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,720
I seem to have only thought about

103
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,980
embracing and identifying with Xiacun,

104
00:05:32,159 --> 00:05:34,560
but I didn't embrace and identify with her.

105
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:35,560
Secretary,

106
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:37,370
what are you talking about?

107
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:40,200
Tolerance and acceptance.

108
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:41,920
Mr. Yin,

109
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:44,090
is this what you want to tell me?

110
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:46,640
I just want to share with you

111
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,860
some of my personal experiences.

112
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,880
If it can inspire you,

113
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,090
that would be great.

114
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:53,560
Back then,

115
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:56,040
promoting the language tutorials

116
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:56,900
wasn't smooth.

117
00:05:57,680 --> 00:06:00,880
Actually, it's not that people don't want to understand.

118
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:03,320
They just need some time and space

119
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:05,440
to build a common language,

120
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:09,280
reach a consensus through trust,

121
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,800
and accomplish something together.

122
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,160
What do you think?

123
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:16,960
I...

124
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:25,920
Hello, everyone.

125
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:28,480
I am Jiao Li, the resident secretary of Xia Village.

126
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,210
First of all,

127
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,360
I want to say sorry to you all.

128
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,720
Our first live stream went very smoothly.

129
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:40,159
The goji berries were sold out,

130
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:41,960
and the farmers were very happy.

131
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:44,140
We packed and shipped them together.

132
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:45,320
We imagined how happy you would be

133
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:47,120
when you ate fresh goji berries

134
00:06:47,159 --> 00:06:48,220
for the first time.

135
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:49,720
We also expected that

136
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:51,640
when the next crop of goji berries ripens,

137
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,560
they could be sent out of Xia Village again.

138
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,960
However, in recent days,

139
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:57,320
we have successively received returns

140
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:58,170
and refunds.

141
00:06:59,159 --> 00:07:00,320
Half of the packages

142
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,610
had problems during transportation.

143
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:05,200
The goji berries we packed with our own hands

144
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:07,240
returned to Xia Village in this way.

145
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:09,040
As the village secretary,

146
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,720
I have an unshirkable responsibility.

147
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,180
Regarding the logistics,

148
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,660
I didn't listen to the team's advice.

149
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:17,800
I blindly handed over the packing work

150
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:20,400
to the farmers who were unfamiliar with the process.

151
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,560
That's what caused such a bad result.

152
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:23,960
At present,

153
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:25,320
we have finished processing

154
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,720
all after-sales orders.

155
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:29,080
We have learned from this experience.

156
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,890
We hope you can give us another chance.

157
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:33,600
We

158
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:35,480
will definitely deliver the goji berry products

159
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,240
perfectly to your hands.

160
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:39,520
Thank you again for your trust,

161
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,600
tolerance, and recognition.

162
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:43,080
Thank you.

163
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:47,120
P.S. When is the second live stream?

164
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,280
I really want to eat fresh goji berries.

165
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:49,960
Oh my.

166
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:51,760
You're making me feel so guilty.

167
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:53,720
Sorry I was too loud earlier. Please don't mind.

168
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:55,980
Face it bravely and stick to your dreams.

169
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,960
The fresh fruit I bought didn't go bad.

170
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,420
Have you made up your mind?

171
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:01,200
Mr. Yin.

172
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:03,290
How did you know what I wanted to do?

173
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:07,300
The big city is definitely different from here.

174
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,280
The methodology you are familiar with

175
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,040
would be hard to even get started here.

176
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:11,970
You are so smart,

177
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,180
of course you know.

178
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:15,800
Jiao Li doesn't just want the villagers

179
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,200
to help pack.

180
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:18,960
He wants to

181
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:20,840
teach them how to fish,

182
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:23,360
so that the fate of goji berries

183
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,760
is in the hands of the people who plant them.

184
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,320
These villagers,

185
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:30,010
Since they are new to these things,

186
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:33,179
you need to give them some time and space.

187
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,200
For so long,

188
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,320
I've been using my old work mindset

189
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,880
to think and act.

190
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:42,159
It was me who didn't accept them.

191
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:45,480
Mr. Yin.

192
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:47,000
I want to hurry back

193
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,120
and solve the problem with everyone.

194
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:49,920
Go.

195
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:31,760
I'm sorry.
